sailpoint.connector
Class AbstractConnector

java.lang.Object
  sailpoint.connector.CollectorServices
      sailpoint.connector.AbstractConnector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Connector
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractFileBasedConnector, JDBCConnector
public abstract class AbstractConnector
extends CollectorServices
implements Connector

A base abstract connector that is intended to be extended by all Connector classes. Extending this class instead of implementing the Connector interface directly will allow the Connector interface to be extended without breaking old code.

All of the Connectors that extend this class will call the one of the two constructors that take an Application and an optional instance. The application object will configure the runtime Attributes and Features of the connector.

This class will implement any new methods that are added over time and in most cases will just throw UnsupportedOperation exception when the methods has been stubbed out.

Along with stubbing out the Connector interface it also provides methods for the following common services:

  • Reading and coercing configuration attributes from Application data
    • CollectorServices.getAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getStringAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getBooleanAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getListAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getEncryptedAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getRequiredAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getRequiredStringAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getRequiredListAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getRequiredEncryptedAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getRequiredListAttribute(String)
    • CollectorServices.getSchemaConfig(Schema, String)
  • Permissions Merging
    • AbstractConnector.mergePermissions(List, List)
  • Map Merging
    • AbstractConnector.mergeMaps(Schema, Map, Map, List)
    • AbstractConnector.defaultMergeMaps(Map, Map, List)
  • Building ResourceObjects from java.util.Map objects
    • AbstractConnector.defaultTransformObject(Schema, Map)
    • AbstractConnector.defaultTransformObject(Schema, Map, boolean)
    • AbstractConnector.defaultTransformObject(Schema, Map, boolean, List)
  • Coercing attribute values based on AttributeDefinition
    • CollectorServices.coerceValue(AttributeDefinition, Object)

See Also:
Application, Attributes, Schema, CollectorServices

The name of the configuration attribute that is used when transforming a Map to ResourceObject in #buildResourceObjectFromMap(Schema schema, Map mergedObject) By default attributes marked multi-valued and in csv format will be transformed from csv to a List of strings.

checkStatus

public ProvisioningResult checkStatus(java.lang.String id)
                               throws sailpoint.connector.ConnectorException,
                                      GeneralException
New in 5.5 this method can be used by async provisioning implementations to check the status of a queued request.

By default this method returns an UnsupportedOperationException.

New in 5.5 this method can be used by asynchronous provisioning implementations to check the status of a queued request.

This method will be called if any of the results returned by the provision method are QUEUED and there is also requestId set on the result.

This method will be called one time for each ProvisioningResult in the ProvisioningPlan. The plan can store results at either the plan, account request or the attribute request level.

The returned result's errors and warnings will be merged back into the main project.

Returning a null result will have no change on the request and it will remained queued.

Specified by:
checkStatus in interface Connector
Parameters:
id - The ID of the queued request.
Returns:
ProvisioningResult that indicates the current status of the request
Throws:
sailpoint.connector.ConnectorException
GeneralException

Helper for checking if the provisioning error can be retried - 1. Check the type of the throwable, if its connection request should be retried 2. getAttributesToRetrieve

protected java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAttributesToRetrieve(java.lang.String objectType,
                                                                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> options)
                                                            throws sailpoint.connector.ConnectorException
A convenience method used to compute which attributes should be included on returned resource objects.

Here is the order they are resolved.

All methods support the following precedence when resolving which attributes should be returned from a connector.

  1. Check the options map for an attribute named "objectAttributeNames"(Connector.OP_ATTRIBUTE_NAMES). These attribute names must be found in the object's schema, any non-schema attributes will be ignored.
  2. If neither of the other two options are specified, connectors should be use the attributes defined in the object's schema map.

Returns:
List containing the name of the attributes
Throws:
sailpoint.connector.ConnectorException

filterPermissions

protected java.util.List<Permission> filterPermissions(java.util.List<Permission> unfiltered)
Default implementation of filtering permissions.

Applications that do not have an optimized way of filtering can use this method. This method will take the un-filtered list and compare it against the Connector.PERMISSION_SCOPE attribute value which is a list of Permissions. if the PERMISSION_SCOPE attribute is non-null then each Permission will be compared against the scoped permissions and filtered if match on target and right.

defaultMergeMaps

public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> defaultMergeMaps(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> obj1,
                                                                                java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> obj2,
                                                                                java.util.List<java.lang.String> mergeAttrs)
Method to merge to map objects, designed initially for use in the DelimitedFileConnector and the JDBCConnector - but general enough for use elsewhere.

Behavior: 1) Obj1 is the master object 2) Any keys found in object2 and not in object1 will be added to object1. If a key is found in both objects but is not in the mergAttrs list 3) object1's attribute will be retained and object2's will be discarded. 4) Any attributes in the mergAttrs list will be merged into a list

buildResourceObjectFromMap

public ResourceObject buildResourceObjectFromMap(Schema schema,
                                                 java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> mergedObject)
Given a Map, build a ResourceObject from the keys/values of the Map. This method will read the configuration and if there is a Connector.CONFIG_TRANSFORMATION_RULE configured it will run the rule. Otherwise, it will run the default map to Resource object conversion method defined.

Returns:
A ResourceObject that represents the data in the map

Build a resource object from a map optionally using the schema attribute definitions to drive coercion. If requested, this method will try to convert csv lists to List objects if the attribute is marked multi-valued. If attrsToLeaveAlone is specified, no transformation takes place for the attributes with these names.

getEffectiveAttribute

protected static java.lang.String getEffectiveAttribute(Schema schema,
                                                        java.lang.String name)
Attempt to find the named attribute in the schema, if its found check if it has an internal name. If the internal name is non-null use it, otherwise if the attribute is not found in the schema or does not have an internal name just return the name.

When an application is using internalName values in the schema this method is needed to designate which attribute should be used to lookup the identity and displayName attributes.

Those values can and typically will be specified using the "name" (vs internalname) of a schema attribute.

Parameters:
schema -
name -
Returns:
the name of the attribute's internal name if non-null otherwise name

logPlan

public void logPlan(ProvisioningPlan src)
Log the XML for a ProvisioningPlan hiding secret data. Unlike openconnector.JsonUtil this is hard to bake into the serialization process. XmlBuilder is functionally similar to JsonBuilder but it is not something allowing direct access, it is buried under XMLObjectFactory. Until the interfaces are reworked, it is easiest to clone the plan and remove things before serialization.

The plan is always logged at "info" level which is what most code uses.
